title: For Sale:  Quite a few rounds of Federal 9mm Luger 115gr FMJ - Gun included (Kahr CM9 + extras)
postcontent:
The concept is simple. You buy this ammo at a crazy inflated price, and I throw in a gun to shoot it with. And some holsters to wear that gun in these different scenarios:
1. Open carry.
2. Winter concealed carry outside waistband with a jacket or long shirt.
3. Anytime concealment inside waistband.
4. Deep concealment on your ankle.

The ammo is Federal 9mm Luger 115gr FMJ, 1000 rounds.
The gun is a Kahr CM9 which functions flawlessly, plus a few holsters.

No, I won't sell the ammo without the gun, this is a package deal. The price is firm. No trades.

The Kahr is in excellent condition. I put about 3500 rounds through it with very few failures. The failures I did have were all with the same 7-round magazine which is known to have issues. I traded that magazine in to Kahr for a 6-round replacement and all was well after that.

Upon reading that the recoil spring assembly is only good for 2000 rounds or so, I replaced it, but never had issues. I have a couple hundred rounds through it with the new recoil assembly on, also with no issues.

It's a great gun but I went with a .380 for a smaller, lighter option and just never use it anymore.

Included in the sale are:
Kahr CM9
Federal 9mm Luger 115gr FMJ - 1000 rounds
2 spare 6-round magazines (3 total)
Blackhawk snap-ring OWB holster
Kusiak IWB holster
Galco ankle holster w/calf strap
Original box and manual, trigger lock.

I am not desperate for cash, so I will not let anyone "take it off my hands" for peanuts.

I'm looking for a no-hassle sale with a reasonable person who knows what he wants and doesn't screw around. If that's you, I'm willing to drive a bit to meet you halfway to make the deal.

For my own protection and peace of mind, I'll need you to have a CPL and WA driver's license. I will take a picture of these at the time of sale, but I won't send in any paperwork to the state. If that doesn't work for you, we can't make a deal.

title: For Sale:  Remington 1100 Ducks & Remington 870 Ducks Unlimited 1st Year for both.
postcontent:
1973 Ducks Unlimited 1100 and 1974 Ducks Unlimited 870. From the "Remington Society"................................................................................................. Remington introduced a special limited edition Model 1100 Ducks Unlimited Commemorative Shotgun, a 12 gauge chambered for 2 3/4" shells with full choke, vent rib 30" barrel. This shotgun was available only in 1973, and was dedicated to the Ducks Unlimited organization. The right side of the receiver was roll-stamped with a simple gold-colored scroll pattern. Centered on the left side of the receiver panel is a multi-colored bronze medallion depicting a canvasback duck, the Ducks Unlimited mallard head logo, flanked by decorative scroll work. At the lower left, stamped in gold-colored script is Remington Model-1100TM and on the lower right is the serial number preceded by DU. Six hundred of these guns were sold directly to DU Chapters for fund raising dinners in 1973, and 10,000 sold conventionally............................................................................................................................ ........................................ As a follow-up to the first year's Remington 1100, DU chose an identically decorated 870 Wingmaster pump as its second Gun of the Year. Introduced in 1950 as a more inexpensively made version of the Model 31, the 870 went on to become a great waterfowling gun and the best-selling shotgun ever made. In 1974 there had already been over 2 million 870s produced, and today that number has climbed to more than 10 million. This DU version of the 870 has a 2 3/4-inch chamber, a 30-inch full-choke barrel, upgraded walnut on the stock and forearm, gold inlaid engraving, and an enameled DU crest on the receiver.

I believe the 1100 to be unfired and have the original hard case for it. The 870 appears to have been loaded and cycled but I am not certain if it was fired or not, I tried to take pictures to show this. They are in close to new condition as it gets with just a few handling marks.

postcontent:
Rare Pistol! This is a Detonics Combat Master .45acp with (2) Detonics 6 round magazines. This particular model is an un-catalogued model with no markings on either side of the slide or on the chamber of the barrel which from the research I have done says its a specialty made pistol for the executives or someone very close to the company heads.  Muzzle is crown cut which is ultra rare on these pistols. I have never seen another barrel cut like it on any of the Detonics I have seen. This pistol is SUPER CLEAN, ULTRA ACCURATE, and a blast to shoot. Trigger is smooth as silk and breaks like a $3,500 Wilson. The gentleman I bought it from 8 years ago had barely shot it and it looked new in box. I have put 400-500 down range and never had an issue. Cash sale preferred at this time, but always open to specialty or hard to find trades. 
This one is stamped Bellevue, WA and all parts have matching serial numbers etched into the gun parts by hand and match the last 3 serial digits. This handmade & assembled custom pistol and was years ahead of the compact 1911 design when it was produced back in the 80's. There are zero MIM(metal injection molding) parts in this pistol. No plastic or other cheap materials. I have tons of pictures and can shoot them if interested. Feel free to TEXT or CALL REDACTED. I have ordered a new WOLFF Recoil spring and firing pin spring just to update the pistol, but they have not been installed yet. title: For Sale:  BEWARE OF SCAMS... DO NOT SEND MONEY VIA PAYPAL !
postcontent:
Recently contacted a member offering a SIG 716 in Dark Earth. The price was too good to be true. Said he was from South Jersey, but gave a Georgia cell phone number and attempted to get me to send him 50% deposit via Paypal. He did not offer a Paypal "username", but instead only had a phone number (same cell #) for the transaction.
I asked for an ebay username to check feedback. The one he provided came up as someone from MA, NOT NJ. Lastly, he send a request for the full amount. When reviewing emails again I noticed the person's use of english to be a little off. All this set off the FRAUD alarms.  DO YOUR RESEARCH and check out the person you're buying from FIRST, before ever sending cash or money. Like this site says.... use a broker or escrow agent! Unfortunately, this site is NOT scammer free...so buyer BEWARE !!!!

Alexander Arms Tactical Blade Trigger $175 shipped and/or A2 Stock for sale

 I just picked up this lower, but didn't want the trigger group or stock.

 As the seller didn't want to break up the lower, I agreed to buy it as a complete lower.

 So I'm parting it out. The trigger group is chromed, unlike the offerings by AA now. The AA price for the trigger group is $203. I'm offering it for $175, but with no pins.  I don't have a price on the A2 stock yet. Make me an offer.
 Thanks for looking.

PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE DO NOT CONTACT ME TO TELL ME THAT YOU CAN FIND THIS ITEM CHEAPER ELSEWHERE. IF YOU WOULD LIKE TO OFFER A LOWER PRICE BECAUSE YOU FOUND ALL OF THESE ITEMS CHEAPER ELSEWHERE, PLEASE PROVIDE THE PROOF. UNTIL THEN, DON'T WASTE YOUR TIME OR MINE WITH SNARKY, UNINFORMED EMAILS. 

Alexander Arms says:

This tactical trigger unit has been designed specifically for field use and does not share a common heritage with a target trigger. For this reason, it is not recommended for target-type shooting, although it may be used with some success in this discipline. The trigger is basically a single stage unit with a bushing mounted disconnector, which is adjustable for engagement and over travel while the pull weight and disconnector engagement are fixed to ensure durability during hard use and inclement environments.

The trigger bow is intentionally narrower than those commonly found on target type triggers. This assists with accurate reference of the trigger finger if the unit is used with gloves or in cold/wet conditions. The pull weight allows manipulation of the trigger with gloves while minimizing the possibility of discharging a round unexpectedly in the manner of a target trigger. In extreme cold conditions the trigger can still be used with mitts with the trigger guard pivoted down, although this is not recommended.

The unit is manufactured from an S7 type tool steel and is through-hardened to provide a durable base. The surface is chrome-plated using a technique that creates a dense finish and a surface hardness in excess of 72 HRC. This surface provides the durability for the trigger in adverse conditions and, hence, the surfaces on both the trigger and the hammer should not be further polished or honed.

title: For Sale:  Palmetto State Armory AR-15 x2 cents
postcontent:
PSA has some deals, most sold out this weekend, but most will be back in stock by Tuesday or Wednesday; be wary of anyone selling genuine PSA stuff (especially uppers), unless you see the logo; PTAC is the bargain brand they sell, and only has a square or box on the uppers; PTAC is usually 100 bucks less than a PSA. They sell AR uppers for around 3-400 bucks, depending upon quality, and lowers complete are in the neighborhood of $150 (blemishes are always minor, most folks would never see them, but QC is strict at PSA).   If curious on a price of something currently sold out, click on "AD TO COMPARE", then click on it again when it shows up to the upper left...just want to help out fellow shooters (from being gouged).  

Last thing, they don't sell "PSA assembled" rifles, with Blackhawk grips, Magpul trigger guards, and standard PSA rear collapsible stocks (even in kits); a lot of what you see are $550 rifles, at best, assembled from various 'other' builds with excess parts...just be aware.  Also, fully-built "ANDERSON" lowers are $175 at Fatboy Tactical in Bixby!
